System for Security Services
1. Introduction:
The aim of this project is to develop a web-based application that assists
security services in locating wanted and missing individuals through face
detection using both video and still images. The system will provide an efficient
and reliable tool to aid in identifying and tracking individuals of interest, thereby
enhancing the overall effectiveness of security operations.
</div>
<div>
2. Problem Description:
The current process of searching for wanted and missing persons is
predominantly manual, time-consuming, and error-prone. Law enforcement
agencies and security services often rely on outdated methods, such as
paper-based flyers and physical search teams, which are ineffective in rapidly
identifying and locating individuals. Additionally, the lack of a centralized
system makes it challenging to collaborate and share information across
different agencies and jurisdictions.
